   "source": [
    "Time-frequency representations\n",
    "==============================\n",
    "\n",
    "Most source separation algorithms do not their operations in the time domain, but rather in the frequency\n",
    "domain. For this, *nussl* provides an interface for working with [Short-Time Fourier Transform (STFT)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Short-time_Fourier_transform>)\n",
    "data. Here, we describe how to do some simple STFT operations with the :class:`nussl.AudioSignal` object. Other time-frequency representations such as the constant-Q transform are not in *nussl* at this time.\n",
    "\n",
    "STFT Basics\n",
    "-----------\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's reinitialize ``signal1`` from the previous page. We should be able to get frequency domain data by looking\n",
    "at ``signal1.stft_data``. Let's try that."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import nussl\n",
    "import time\n",
    "start_time = time.time()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Matching file found at /home/pseetharaman/.nussl/audio/schoolboy_fascination_excerpt.wav, skipping download.\n",
      "STFT Data: None\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "input_file_path = nussl.efz_utils.download_audio_file(\n",
    "    'schoolboy_fascination_excerpt.wav')\n",
    "signal1 = nussl.AudioSignal(input_file_path)\n",
    "print('STFT Data:', signal1.stft_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Whoops! Because this object was initialized from a .wav file (i.e., time-series data), this :class:`AudioSignal`: object has\n",
    "no frequency domain data by default. To populate it with frequency data we do thusly:\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(1025, 1293, 2)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "stft = signal1.stft()\n",
    "print(stft.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Aha! Now we can examine how STFT data is stored in the :class:`AudioSignal`: object. \n",
    "Similar to ``signal1.audio_data``, STFT data is stored in a (complex-valued) \n",
    "numpy array called ``signal1.stft_data``.\n",
    "\n",
    "By inspecting the shape we see that the first dimension represents the number of FFT bins taken at each hop,\n",
    "the second represents the length of our signal (in hops), and the third dimension is number of channels.\n",
    "\n",
    "We can also get power spectrogram data from our signal as well. As we would expect, this is the same\n",
    "shape as ``signal1.stft_data``."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(1025, 1293, 2)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# np.abs(signal1.stft_data) ** 2\n",
    "psd = signal1.power_spectrogram_data\n",
    "print(psd.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's take a look at the spectrogram, using some helpful functions from `nussl.utils`, with different settings on the `y_axis`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x648 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 9))\n",
    "plt.subplot(311)\n",
    "plt.title('Linear-frequency spectrogram')\n",
    "nussl.utils.visualize_spectrogram(signal1)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(312)\n",
    "plt.title('Log-frequency spectrogram')\n",
    "nussl.utils.visualize_spectrogram(signal1, y_axis='log')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(313)\n",
    "plt.title('Mel-frequency spectrogram')\n",
    "nussl.utils.visualize_spectrogram(signal1, y_axis='mel')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Inverse STFTs\n",
    "-------------\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's do something a little more interesting with our :class:`AudioSignal`: object. Since ``signal1.stft_data`` is just\n",
    "a regular numpy array, we can access and manipulate it as such. So let's implement a low pass filter by creating a\n",
    "new :class:`AudioSignal`: object and leaving ``signal1`` unaltered.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's eliminate all frequencies above about 400 Hz in our signal.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "lp_stft = signal1.stft_data.copy()\n",
    "lp_cutoff = 1000  # Hz\n",
    "frequency_vector = signal1.freq_vector  # a vector of frequency values for each FFT bin\n",
    "idx = (np.abs(frequency_vector - lp_cutoff)).argmin()  # trick to find the index of the closest value to lp_cutoff\n",
    "lp_stft[idx:, :, :] = 0.0j  # every freq above lp_cutoff is 0 now"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Okay, so now we have low passed STFT data in the numpy array ``lp_stft``. Now we are going to see how we can initialize\n",
    "a new :class:`AudioSignal`: object using this data. Let's make a copy of the original signal, `signal1`, using its helper function\n",
    "`make_copy_with_stft_data`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Audio Data: None\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "signal1_lp = signal1.make_copy_with_stft_data(lp_stft)\n",
    "print('Audio Data:', signal1_lp.audio_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Easy-peasy! Now ``signal1_lp`` is a new :class:`AudioSignal`: object that has been initialized with STFT data instead of\n",
    "time series data. But there's no audio data to listen to! Before we can hear the result, we need to do an Inverse STFT to get back time-series data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "\n",
       "                <audio  controls=\"controls\" >\n",
       "                    <source src=\"data:audio/mpeg;base64,\" type=\"audio/mpeg\" />\n",
       "                    Your browser does not support the audio element.\n",
       "                </audio>\n",
       "              "
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.lib.display.Audio object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "AudioSignal (unlabeled): 15.000 sec @ /home/pseetharaman/.nussl/audio/schoolboy_fascination_excerpt.wav, 44100 Hz, 2 ch.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "signal1_lp.istft()\n",
    "signal1_lp.embed_audio()\n",
    "print(signal1_lp)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's check out what the spectrogram looks like."
   ]
  },

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))\n",
    "plt.title('Masked spectrogram')\n",
    "nussl.utils.visualize_spectrogram(signal1_lp, y_axis='mel')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Cool beans!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "STFT Parameters\n",
    "---------------\n",
    "\n",
    "Where did the STFT parameters for our audio signals come from? There are three main arguments for taking an STFT:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. `window_length`: How long are the windows within which to take the FFT?\n",
    "2. `hop_length`: How much to hop between windows?\n",
    "3. `window_type`: What sort of windowing function to use?\n",
    "\n",
    "These three parameters are grouped into a `namedtuple` object that \n",
    "belongs to every AudioSignal object. This is the `STFTParams` object:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "nussl.core.audio_signal.STFTParams"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nussl.STFTParams"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "When we created the audio signals above, the STFT parameters were built on initialization:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "STFTParams(window_length=2048, hop_length=512, window_type='sqrt_hann')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "signal1.stft_params"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The STFT parameters are built using helpful defaults based on properties of the audo signal. \n",
    "32 millisecond windows are used with an 8 millisecond hop between windows. At 44100 Hz, \n",
    "this results in 2048 for the window length and 512 for the hop length. The window \n",
    "type is the `sqrt_hann` window, which generally has better separation performance. \n",
    "There are many windows that can be used:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['hamming', 'rectangular', 'hann', 'blackman', 'triang', 'sqrt_hann']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nussl.constants.ALL_WINDOWS"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "An AudioSignal's STFT parameters can be set after the fact. Let's change the one for signal1:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(129, 5169, 2)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "signal1.stft_params = nussl.STFTParams(\n",
    "    window_length=256, hop_length=128)\n",
    "signal1.stft().shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The shape of the resultant STFT is now different. Note that 256 resulted in 129 \n",
    "frequencies of analysis per frame. In general, the rule is `(window_length // 2) + 1`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Time taken: 7.7818 seconds\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "end_time = time.time()\n",
    "time_taken = end_time - start_time\n",
    "print(f'Time taken: {time_taken:.4f} seconds')"
   ]
